          "date": "2015-01-09 00:32:09.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "subject": "LU-6100 mdd: Not set xattr if object is DEAD",
        "message": "LU-6100 mdd: Not set xattr if object is DEAD\n\nIf the object is already being unlinked, do not set xattr,\notherwise the race might happen between the close and reint\noperation (like set xattr), because close will unlink the\norphan, but not enqueue ldlm locks. Especially if the unlinked\nobject is striped directory.\n\nSigned-off-by: wang di <di.wang@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ia43c82ce86338f1c05ce452146ff000a16425f85\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
